dcterms:creator: J. Ferryman
dcterms:description: The PETS09-S2L1 sequence consists of 799 frames of 768 × 576 pixels recorded at 7 frames per second with medium crowd density.
dcterms:title: PETS09-S2L1

dcterms:creator: J. Ferryman
dcterms:description: The PETS09-S2L2 sequence consists of 442 frames with the same resolution and frame rate as the PETS09-S2L1 sequence, but it contains heavy crowd density and illumination changes.
dcterms:title: PETS09-S2L2

dcterms:creator: G. Shu
A. Dehghan
O. Oreifej
E. Hand
M. Shah
dcterms:description: The UCF Parking Lot dataset consists of 998 frames of 1920 × 1080 pixels recorded at 29 frames per second with medium crowd density, long-term occlusion, and targets of similar appearance.
dcterms:title: UCF Parking Lot (UCF-PL)

dcterms:creator: Y. Wu
X. Tong
Y. Zhang
H. Lu
dcterms:description: The Soccer dataset consists of 155 frames of 960 × 544 pixels recorded at 3 to 5 frames per second, featuring heavy occlusion, sudden change of motion direction of players, high similarity among players of the same team, and scale changes.
dcterms:title: Soccer dataset

dcterms:creator: B. Benfold
I. Reid
dcterms:description: The Town Center dataset consists of 4500 frames of 1080 × 1920 pixels recorded at 25 frames per second, containing medium crowd density, heavy occlusion, and scale changes.
dcterms:title: Town Center dataset

dcterms:creator: S. Sivaraman
M. Trivedi
dcterms:description: The Urban sequence from the LISA 2010 dataset contains car images of 704 × 480 collected at 30 frames per second from a camera mounted on a moving vehicle, captured from an urban area with low traffic density on a cloudy day.
dcterms:title: Urban sequence from LISA 2010 dataset

dcterms:creator: S. Sivaraman
M. Trivedi
dcterms:description: The Sunny sequence from the LISA 2010 dataset contains car images of 704 × 480 collected at 30 frames per second from a camera mounted on a moving vehicle, captured from a highway with medium traffic density on a sunny day.
dcterms:title: Sunny sequence from LISA 2010 dataset
